        "timestamp": 1757007341
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>basically I think this is the formula for circumcenter in barycentric coordinates</p>",
        "id": 537722025,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757007465
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would be grateful, at this moment my brain doesn't cooperate. <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 537722028,
        "sender_full_name": "Ilmārs Cīrulis",
        "timestamp": 1757007468
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>which for a triangle ABC the circumcenter is (sin 2A, sin 2B, sin 2C) where A B C are the angles</p>",
        "id": 537722175,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757007537
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so let ABC be a triangle and let α β γ be its angles then the circumcenter <code>O</code> is given by <code>O = (A*sin 2α + B*sin 2β + C*sin2γ) / (sin 2α + sin 2β + sin 2γ)</code></p>",
        "id": 537723259,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757007982
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in this case of course the circumcenter is <code>0</code></p>",
        "id": 537723308,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757008002
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and you apply the intercepted arc double angle thing to get angles in the triangle</p>",
        "id": 537723388,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1757008046
    },
    {
